position summary
the regeneron genetics center is a wholly-owned subsidiary of the company organized to collaborate with health system and research group to elucidate on a large scale genetic factor that cause or influence a range of human disease building upon regeneron's strength in mouse genetics and genetics-driven drug discovery and development the center will specialize in ultra-high-throughput exome sequencing and computational biology discovery of genotype-phenotype association through linkage to well-annotated de-identified patient electronic medical record and validation of discovery using regenerons velocigene technology our interest encompass a breadth of different area such a mendelian and family framework large-scale population genetics both common and rare variant and gene-gene interaction program goal include target discovery indication discovery and patient-disease stratification objectives include advancing basic science around the world through public sharing of discovery providing clinically-valuable insight to physician and patient of collaborating health-care system and identifying novel target for drug development
